<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef" CalDefCategory="DriverWorkload" Description="Calibration Definition for GIS-337 Driver Workload Based Lockouts and Touchscreen fidelity configuration  ">
  <CalDefFileVersion>7</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <Date>5/20/2015</Date>
    <Description>Initial release of Calibration Definition includes Driver Workload Lockouts for Apple CarPlay and Android Auto. The values represented here for each binary caldef reflect the default calibration as described in GIS-337 Appendix C</Description>
    <Author>Nikhil Neti</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>11/19/2015</Date>
    <Description>Added Apple_CarPlay_japanMaps &amp; Apple_CarPlay_touchFidelity cals for Apple CarPlay. The values represented here for each caldef reflect the default calibration as described in GIS-337 Appendix C.</Description>
    <Author>Nikhil Neti</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>6/10/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS337_ConsumerDeviceProjection.caldef file, added Apple_CarPlay_enableWireless calibration for the CarPlay over Wireless feature to support to support RTC CR#: 1431345. Also, added AndroidAuto_enableWireless calibration to protect for the calibration that will be needed for model year TBD when wireless Android Auto feature will be implemented. Also, updated the usage field for all of the calibrations in this caldef file to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>10/1/2017</Date>
    <Description>Added GEM usage to all of the calibrations in the GIS337_ConsumerDeviceProjection.caldef file. Since all of these calibrations fell within the current criteria of requiring GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>11/17/2017</Date>
    <Description>For CR#: 1635297 within the GIS337_ConsumerDeviceProjection.caldef file, added one new calibration (Apple_CarPlay_Location) for use by the F-Ten Info3 Low Radio supplier.</Description>
    <Author>Shanmukh Kandala</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>09/14/2018</Date>
    <Description>Per CR#1582808, updated GIS337_ConsumerDeviceProjection.caldef by adding Android.Auto_VEC_Whitelist calibration.</Description>
    <Author>Shanmukh Kandala</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>7</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
